result.execSummary:
The defendant Ryan James Taylor was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Ryan James Taylor is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Ryan James Taylor was found guilty of Criminal Trespass to Dwelling, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.14(2).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Case called at 11:48 AM.  Defendant Ryan James Taylor in court with attorney Timothy Luke Angel.  Jenna L Gill appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Angel informs the Court Defendant paid restitution this AM.  Attorney Angel files Amended Information, and Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights form with the Court.  Court questions Defendant regarding the Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights form.  Court questions Attorney Angel regarding the Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights form.  Parties stipulate to factual basis.  Court is satisfied Defendant enters his plea freely, voluntarily, intelligently, and knowingly and accepts his plea of No Contest, adjudicating him Guilty.  State makes a statement to the Court.  State also informs the Court Defendant has paid restitution in full.  Attorney Angel makes a statement to the Court.  Defendant makes a statement to the Court.  Court will accept the proposed plea agreement and Order:  $100.00 fine + costs, dismiss count 1, allow 60 DTP, failure to pay-jail time.
